# ORIG TITLE    Yordanov returns gold . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Bulgarian legend Valentin Yordanov sent back his Olympic gold medal from the 1996 Atlanta Games on Wednesday, to protest the International Olympic Committee’s decision to drop wrestling from the Olympic program. The 53-year-old is the president of the Bulgarian wrestling federation and won an unprecedented 10 world championship medals during his career. Some of Bulgarian wrestling’s biggest names have already expressed their support for Yordanov, saying they believed that the IOC would scrap the plans to drop the sport. The plans have to be ratified in September. Wrestling has been Bulgaria’s most successful Olympic sport with the country’s athletes winning a total of 16 titles. 
